/// token is assigned to `currentToken` BEFORE the worker `Task` is spawned, so
/// any subsequent supersession or cancellation can compare against it. Every
/// single write to published state (`isRunning`, `isCancelling`,
/// `lastScanStartedAt`, `lastScanEndedAt`, `lastErrorMessage`, `lastRunStatus`)
/// inside the worker task is guarded by `guard currentToken == myToken else { return }` — this
/// guarantees that a superseded "zombie" run can never clobber the state of a
/// newer run.
///
/// The subprocess itself is launched inside `withTaskCancellationHandler`. The
/// `onCancel` closure runs on an arbitrary executor, so the `Process` reference
/// is held inside an `OSAllocatedUnfairLock`.
///
/// `cancelScan()` is deliberately **synchronous** and does NOT `await` anything.
/// It fires `currentTask?.cancel()` and returns immediately.
